"{\"24\":\"Distress and anguish fill him with terror; they overwhelm him, like a king poised to attack,\",\"25\":\"because he shakes his fist at God and vaunts himself against the Almighty,\",\"26\":\"defiantly charging against him with a thick, strong shield.\",\"27\":\"\\\"Though his face is covered with fat and his waist bulges with flesh,\",\"20\":\"All his days the wicked man suffers torment, the ruthless through all the years stored up for him.\",\"21\":\"Terrifying sounds fill his ears; when all seems well, marauders attack him.\",\"22\":\"He despairs of escaping the darkness; he is marked for the sword.\",\"23\":\"He wanders about-food for vultures; he knows the day of darkness is at hand.\",\"28\":\"he will inhabit ruined towns and houses where no one lives, houses crumbling to rubble.\",\"29\":\"He will no longer be rich and his wealth will not endure, nor will his possessions spread over the land.\",\"1\":\"Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:\",\"3\":\"Would he argue with useless words, with speeches that have no value?\",\"2\":\"\\\"Would a wise man answer with empty notions or fill his belly with the hot east wind?\",\"5\":\"Your sin prompts your mouth; you adopt the tongue of the crafty.\",\"4\":\"But you even undermine piety and hinder devotion to God.\",\"7\":\"\\\"Are you the first man ever born? Were you brought forth before the hills?\",\"6\":\"Your own mouth condemns you, not mine; your own lips testify against you.\",\"9\":\"What do you know that we do not know? What insights do you have that we do not have?\",\"8\":\"Do you listen in on God's council? Do you limit wisdom to yourself?\",\"11\":\"Are God's consolations not enough for you, words spoken gently to you?\",\"10\":\"The gray-haired and the aged are on our side, men even older than your father.\",\"13\":\"so that you vent your rage against God and pour out such words from your mouth?\",\"12\":\"Why has your heart carried you away, and why do your eyes flash,\",\"15\":\"If God places no trust in his holy ones, if even the heavens are not pure in his eyes,\",\"14\":\"\\\"What is man, that he could be pure, or one born of woman, that he could be righteous?\",\"17\":\"\\\"Listen to me and I will explain to you; let me tell you what I have seen,\",\"16\":\"how much less man, who is vile and corrupt, who drinks up evil like water!\",\"19\":\"(to whom alone the land was given when no alien passed among them):\",\"18\":\"what wise men have declared, hiding nothing received from their fathers\",\"31\":\"Let him not deceive himself by trusting what is worthless, for he will get nothing in return.\",\"30\":\"He will not escape the darkness; a flame will wither his shoots, and the breath of God's mouth will carry him away.\",\"35\":\"They conceive trouble and give birth to evil; their womb fashions deceit.\\\"\",\"34\":\"For the company of the godless will be barren, and fire will consume the tents of those who love bribes.\",\"33\":\"He will be like a vine stripped of its unripe grapes, like an olive tree shedding its blossoms.\",\"32\":\"Before his time he will be paid in full, and his branches will not flourish.\"}"